In[3]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

np.random.seed(0)
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))

ax1 = fig.add_subplot(2, 3, 1)
x = np.linspace(0, 2*np.pi, 400)
y = np.sin(x)
ax1.plot(x, y, color='blue')
ax1.set_title("    ")
ax1.set_xlabel("x")
ax1.set_ylabel("sin(x)")

ax2 = fig.add_subplot(2, 3, 2, projection='3d')
X = np.linspace(-5, 5, 50)
Y = np.linspace(-5, 5, 50)
X, Y = np.meshgrid(X, Y)
Z = np.sin(np.sqrt(X**2 + Y**2))
ax2.plot_surface(X, Y, Z, cmap='viridis')
ax2.set_title("   (3d)")
ax2.set_xlabel("X")
ax2.set_ylabel("Y")
ax2.set_zlabel("Z")

ax3 = fig.add_subplot(2, 3, 3)
x_scatter = np.random.rand(100)
y_scatter = np.random.rand(100)
ax3.scatter(x_scatter, y_scatter, color='red', alpha=0.6)
ax3.set_title("")
ax3.set_xlabel("X")
ax3.set_ylabel("Y")

ax4 = fig.add_subplot(2, 3, 4)
data = np.random.randn(1000)
ax4.hist(data, bins=30, color='green', alpha=0.7)
ax4.set_title("")
ax4.set_xlabel("")
ax4.set_ylabel("")

ax5 = fig.add_subplot(2, 3, 5)
categories = ['A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'E']
values = np.random.randint(1, 10, size=len(categories))
ax5.bar(categories, values, color='purple', alpha=0.8)
ax5.set_title(" ")
ax5.set_xlabel("")
ax5.set_ylabel("")

ax6 = fig.add_subplot(2, 3, 6)
pie_values = np.random.randint(1, 10, size=len(categories))
ax6.pie(pie_values, labels=categories, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
ax6.set_title(" ")

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

_, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(10, 6)) 

axes[0, 0].plot(x, np.sin(x)) # 0, 0 --   
axes[0, 0].set_title("sin(x)")

axes[0, 1].plot(x, np.cos(x)) # 0, 1 --    
axes[0, 1].set_title("cos(x)")

axes[1, 0].plot(x, np.tan(x))
axes[1, 0].set_title("tan(x)")

axes[1, 1].plot(x, np.sinh(x))
axes[1, 1].set_title("sinh(x)")

plt.tight_layout() #    ,  
plt.show()

In[14]:
x = np.linspace(0, 10, 100)
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))

fig_cells = (2, 2) #  ""  

ax1_place = (0, 0) #     ""
# ,     
#      `rowspan`
ax1 = plt.subplot2grid(fig_cells, ax1_place, colspan=2)
ax1.plot(x, np.sin(x))
ax1.set_title("sin(x)   ")

ax2_place = (1, 0) # ()  
ax2 = plt.subplot2grid(fig_cells, ax2_place) #   1 
ax2.plot(x, np.cos(x))
ax2.set_title("cos(x)")

ax3_place = (1, 1)
ax3 = plt.subplot2grid(fig_cells, ax3_place)
ax3.plot(x, np.tan(x))
ax3.set_title("tan(x)")

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
